'''Somalia Mogadishu and Its Banaadir Hinterlands'''

In the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries, the southern city of Mogadishu became Somalia's most important city. Mogadishu, Marka, and Baraawe, had been major Somali coastal towns in medieval times
